title: She's looking Rosie! Helen Flanagan sports skimpy outfit to bake cakes ahead of Coronation Street return
text:
TV She's looking Rosie! Helen Flanagan sports skimpy outfit to bake cakes ahead of Coronation Street return There's no denying it, the 26-year-old actress has certainly regained her figure since she had her own bun in the oven in these saucy snaps Share Helen wears a rubber crop top and complementary saucily-positioned pinny (Photo: Karis Kennedy) Share Get soaps   Thank you for subscribing!   
There's no way you’re getting a job in Roy’s Rolls in that outfit, chuck – even if you have borrowed Hilda Ogden’s rollers. 
Yes, here’s Helen Flanagan ahead of her return to Coronation Street , dressed in a skimpy outfit to bake some cakes. 
A rubber crop top – ahem, a vital accessory for any self-respecting baker – is complemented by a saucily-positioned pinny which fails to keep much covered. 
In another shot she wears pink again – plus white retro boots – as she poses in a launderette. As you do. Read More The actress wears another pink outfit with retro white boots as shes poses in a launderette (Photo: Karis Kennedy) Rosie Webster breezes in from Miami with TV sister Sophie when Helen returns to Corrie (Photo: ITV) 
But there’s no denying it, 26-year-old Helen has certainly regained her figure since she had her own bun in the oven. 
Helen and Celtic soccer star boyfriend Scott Sinclair, 27, had baby Matilda back in 2015. 
The actress left Corrie five years ago but is back this week as her character Rosie Webster breezes in from Miami with TV sis Sophie, played by Brooke Vincent, 24. Read More Helen's character Rosie is suspected by police of drug trafficking (Photo: ITV) Helen left Corrie five years ago but is back on our screens as Rosie Webster (Photo: ITV) 
As soap fans know, things are rarely straightforward for the Websters and Rosie – wearing a crop top on TV too – is suspected by police of drug trafficking. 
Drugs? Nah. That white powder on the counter is definitely flour. Like us on Facebook
